// Exercises non-entry-block parameter rooting: a ref-typed value is
// carried across the loop back-edge as a block parameter (not a
// fresh-each-iteration instruction result). The Cranelift backend's
// `emit_block_param_roots` non-entry branch must root the loop-header
// block's String parameter on every iteration, otherwise the
// accumulated string would be swept once the auto-collect threshold
// trips and the next concat would read freed memory.
//
// `acc` accumulates "x" once per iteration. After 50000 iterations
// the final string is 50000 bytes long. Each concat produces a fresh
// allocation that becomes the new `acc`, so the loop allocates well
// past the 1-MB auto-collect threshold and the GC fires many times
// while `acc` is the only live root chain.
function main() {
  let mut acc: String = ""
  let mut i: Int = 0
  while (i < 50000) {
    acc = acc + "x"
    i = i + 1
  }
  print(acc.length())
}
